question.text: Power supplied to a particle of mass <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>kg</mi></math> varies with time as <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi><mo>⁡</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><msup><mi mathvariant="normal">t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant="normal">W</mi></math>, where <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi mathvariant="normal">t</mi></math> is in seconds. If the velocity of the particle at <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi mathvariant="normal">t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> is <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi mathvariant="normal">v</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>, then what is the velocity (in <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi mathvariant="normal">m</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant="normal">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>) of the particle at <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi mathvariant="normal">t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant="normal">s</mi></math>?

solution.text: <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mtable columnspacing="1em" rowspacing="4pt" columnalign="left"><mtr><mtd><msub><mi mathvariant="normal">K</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">f</mi></msub><mo>−</mo><msub><mi mathvariant="normal">K</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">i</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mo>∫</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi><mo>⋅</mo><mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">t</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi mathvariant="normal">m</mi><msup><mi mathvariant="normal">v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>−</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>=</mo><msubsup><mo>∫</mo><mn>0</mn><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msup><mi mathvariant="normal">t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>)</mo></mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">t</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo><msup><mi mathvariant="normal">v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msubsup><mrow><mo>[</mo><mfrac><msup><mi mathvariant="normal">t</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>]</mo></mrow><mn>0</mn><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi mathvariant="normal">v</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant="normal">m</mi><msup><mi mathvariant="normal">s</mi><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></mtd></mtr></mtable></math>
